<br>
I know the North, South, and Mid Spires have camp rules on them, but aren't the hills on the back a free for all area?<br>
<br>
As a 32 Wizard, it's pretty hard to get in a group in SKarana due to the level, but these gnolls still give me great exp, as long as I have Sow potions with me... it's a safe hunt.<br>
<br>
But so often I'd camp the back hills only to see other groups who have the spires camped pull from there.  What pisses me off is when I snare a gnoll and then somebody intercepts it as it goes after me and then I'm the one who is accused of KSing.<br>
<br>
What are the rules back here, and since I snared first, doesn't it make that mob mine?  I'm weary about calling a GM since I'm soloing and it's my word against 2 to 6 peoples.<br>
<br>
Anybody had this experience... Help please.  Thank you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uazlinon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azlinon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 7:31:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eq.guildmagic.com/pics/6029.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camp Rules: SK Paw Spires</span><hr size=1> Ok, in any case, the first person to agro a mob has claimed it.  That was decided by Verant, and is whay they are supposed to use in determining KS incidents.  Camp locations vary depending on server.  On Terris-Thule, the hill is a camp.  On servers that follow first come first server (FCFS), the first group capable of taking on the mob(s) and making their intentions known has the camp.  So for instance, if you went down to Kedge looking for Phinny, and an uberguild shows up and says they are taking him, you have the rights to it even if they get there first (provided you told them you were going to kill him).  Don't expect them to honor it, but that is the rule.  Now, the rest of the servers have a reservation system.  I highly doubt anyone would post a camp or event for the hill in SK, but if they were and your server honors reservations, that person has it.  If a guild posted that they were going to camp the Paw entrance in Sk for example, you would have to honor it in that case, even if you got there first.  You really need to check to see how your server is set-up though. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=6029">Azlinon Seflarian</a> of <a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/divinesymphony">Divine Symphony</a><br>
Guild-Leader<br>
Wizard of Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 9:31:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camp Rules: SK Paw Spires</span><hr size=1> From my experience there a LONG time ago, people were generally overpowered for the spires and would try to grab any gnoll they could.  Some group on the north spires would claim the hill one day, the next day the middle spires would claim it.  <br>
<br>
Try to work something out with that group that &quot;claims&quot; the hill gnolls. Talk to them politely. If you really want the gnolls there you can /petition and envoke PNP to make them share. You have every right to kill those gnolls, its just in bad taste to envoke PNP to get mobs that someone else is camping. <br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
 <p><center>
Luminea Manaburn <BR>
52 Channeler<BR>
Drunks of Tunare <BR>

