</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mordeeve>Mordeeve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 1:20:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camp Rules: SK Paw Spires</span><hr size=1> -Bah just use good manners. Please dont pull from the hill I am camping it because the South Spire is taken<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Mordeeve Zal'Yothmodok///53rd Circle Gnome Wizard</b> <i>///SPIRIT LURKERS//Cazic Thule Server</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iudar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 2:06:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camp Rules: SK Paw Spires</span><hr size=1> Get your click stick (SoTF)...<br>
<br>
Once you snare a mob, rapid click it.  If someone tries to take it:<br>
<br>
1:  It's glowing red.  It's clearly been engaged, and they can be petitioned (if you desire).<br>
<br>
<br>
2:  If someone does try to steal it, you can pull it's attention back to you in seconds.<br>
<br>
<br>
If they whine bitch and moan (and they will) tell them outright that you had already engaged it, and you were merely ensuring your kill.<br>
<br>
<br>
No-one has KSd my group since I got it.<br>
<br>
/wave mob<br>
<br>
Hey, I&quot;m over here!<br>
<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
CLICK<br>
<br>
<br>
You say to your party:  Oh yeah, he's REALLY pissed off now!<br>
<br>
<br>
Becareful not to badly over agro, or the tanks won't be able to taunt it off you (only a trouble when you can't kite).<br>
<br>
<br>
Solo though, they will not kill steal you without Wizardly Assistence.  You'll get too much agro, and dump too much damage too fast for them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=81.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=84.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=88.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=88.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=88.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=88.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option